The Rocchio Algorithm for Relevance Feedback:
\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout

}
\end_layout

\end_inset

 The Rocchio algorithm 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Salton1971"

\end_inset

 is a classic algorithm of relevance feedback used mainly for query expansion.
 In brief, it provides a method of incorporating relevance feedback information
 into the vector space model representing a query 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Manning2008"

\end_inset

.
 The underlying theory behind Rocchio is to find a query vector 
\begin_inset Formula $\overrightarrow{Q'}$
\end_inset

, that maximizes similarity with relevant documents while minimizing similarity
 with irrelevant documents.
 Typically, a pseudo-relevance feedback (PRF) set of 
\begin_inset Formula $k$
\end_inset

 top ranked documents obtained after an initial run of the query is considered
 as the set of relevant documents to build 
\begin_inset Formula $\overrightarrow{Q'}$
\end_inset

.
 We refer to this method as RocchioQE.
\begin_inset Foot
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
We used the LucQE module, which provides an implementation of the Rocchio
 method for Lucene.
 
\family typewriter
http://lucene-qe.sourceforge.net/
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Similarly, Rocchio can be used as a QR method.
 Basically, the idea is that once the Rocchio-modified query vector has
 been computed, it is possible to select only the terms that appear in the
 initial query 
\begin_inset Formula $Q$
\end_inset

 and rank them using the Rocchio score and finally, select the top 
\begin_inset Formula $k$
\end_inset

 terms with the highest score to build 
\begin_inset Formula $Q'$
\end_inset

.
 We refer to this approach as RocchioQR.
\end_layout

