\end_inset

 Magdy et al.
 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "Magdy2011"

\end_inset

 proposed a patent query expansion method, which automatically generates
 candidate synonym sets (SynSet) for terms to use as a source of expansion
 terms.
 The idea for generating the SynSet comes from the characteristics of the
 CLEF-IP patent collection, where some of the sections in some patents are
 translated into three languages (English, French, and German).
 They used these parallel manual translations to create possible synonyms
 sets.
 Hence, for a word 
\begin_inset Formula $w$
\end_inset

 in one language which has possible translations to a set of words in another
 language 
\begin_inset Formula ${w_{1},w_{2},\ldots,w_{n}}$
\end_inset

, this set of words can be considered as synonyms or at least related to
 each other.
 The generated SynSet is used for query expansion in two ways: (i) The first
 one used the probability associated with the SynSet entries as a weight
 for each expanded term in the query (denoted WSynSet).
 Therefore, each term was replaced with its SynSet entries with the probability
 of each item in the SynSet acting as a weight to the term within the query.
 (ii) The second one neglected this associated probability and used uniform
 weighting for all synonyms of a given term (denoted USynSet).
\end_layout

